\i0  gene expression. How might you test your hypothesis?\
\
Intronic variants could lead to changes in epigenetic regulation; for example, if an intron was mutated such that some non-cytosine base pairs flipped to cytosine, then the region could become more methylated, possibly preventing gene expression. One way to test this would to be to see if the mutated intron had significantly more cytosine base pairs than the non-mutated intron.\
