One case where a transcription factor cannot bind to the consensus sequence occurs in the Lac Operon, where the promoter cannot bind to the promoter sequence if the repressor is bound to the cap site. So, there is at least one case where a transcription factor can\'92t bind to a promoter sequence even when they share a consensus sequence.\
